ğŸ’¡ This project shows how unsupervised ML + business logic can empower smarter decisions for marketing, retention, and growth.

In this customer segmentation project, I built a complete machine learning pipeline to analyze and segment retail customers based on their purchasing behavior. Using the Online Retail dataset, I performed exploratory data analysis (EDA), cleaned and preprocessed the data, and engineered key features using the RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) model. I then applied dimensionality reduction using PCA and experimented with multiple unsupervised learning algorithms such as KMeans, DBSCAN, and Gaussian Mixture Models (GMM) to identify distinct customer segments. The results showed that KMeans produced the most meaningful clusters with high silhouette scores, revealing actionable groups like loyal customers, low spenders, and at-risk buyers. Visualizations were used to compare clustering outputs, and the insights can help businesses drive targeted marketing strategies. In the future, this project could be enhanced by incorporating product-level or time-based features and deploying it via Streamlit or Flask for real-time applications. If youâ€™re interested in trying this project yourself, feel free to visit my Kaggle and GitHub repositories.

